      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral third-party service that holds all the financial documents and funds for your home transaction until the closing date is reached. It ensures that the seller receives their money only after the title is transferred to you, and that you receive the keys only after the seller's funds are wired to them. Your realtor is likely recommending this because it protects both parties from fraud and ensures a smooth, secure transfer of ownership in Toronto. Without escrow, there would be a risk that the seller might not get paid or you might not get the deed, so it is a standard safety measure for the closing process. You will need to provide a deposit to the escrow agent to cover their fees, which are typically bundled into your final closing costs.",
