      "content": "Yes, you can think of it that way, but it's more accurate to say the escrow agent is a trusted intermediary who holds the funds and documents until all conditions are met. In Toronto, this is usually a title company, a mortgage lender, or a specialized escrow service rather than a standard bank account you have direct access to. You will likely sign a separate agreement with them to open this account, and the money sits there safely until the final closing documents are signed. This separation ensures that neither the buyer nor the seller can touch the funds prematurely.",
